Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation:

**1. Register the route:**
```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute("ProductDetailsPage", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage (both approaches):**
```csharp
// Simple string parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"ProductDetailsPage?productId={product.Id}");

// Complex object via dictionary
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("ProductDetailsPage", new Dictionary<string, object>
{
    { "product", selectedProduct }
});
```

**3. Receive data in your ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**
```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty] private string _productId;
    [ObservableProperty] private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Simple string parameter (comes in as string)
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
            ProductId = id.ToString();

        // Complex object (preserved as original type)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
            Product = p;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| **Syntax** | interpolated URI | `Dictionary<string, object>` overload |
| **Type** | arrives as `string` | arrives as original type — cast it |
| **Deep-link safe** | ✅ yes | ❌ no (in-memory only) |

Use string parameters for deep-linkable, serializable values. Use the dictionary overload when you need the full object and don't need deep-link support.
